&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End of Life Facilitator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to work a 6 month fixed term contract as End of Life Facilitator for the intermediate care beds in Essex Inpatients Units working across Brentwood Community Hospital and Thurrock Community Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The End of Life Care Facilitator (EoLCF) will be the Clinical Lead for end of life care and support patients, their families and carers by providing learning and development opportunities for staff caring for people in their last year of life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The EoLCF will work in conjunction with the Hospital Palliative and Supportive Care Team and the Community Teams as well as the quality and safety team to facilitate a bedside learning approach to meet the training needs of the workforce. The EoLCF will be responsible for evaluating the impact of training opportunities to inform further teaching/training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High Cost Area Supplement – Essex&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post also attracts payment for High Cost Area Supplement of 5% of the basic salary (with a minimum of £1,034 to a maximum of £1,791)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePhathi NyathiJob titleModern MatronEmail addressphathi.nyathi@nelft.nhs.ukTelephone number07713 089294Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information or an informal chat, please contact Phathi Nyathi on 07713 089294 or email Phathi.Nyathi@nelft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
